lightly doped drain region benefits: reduced in the channel/body region (since a larger fraction of the pn-junction depletion region resides within the drain) and lower peak electric field at the drain junction. The short-channel effect would be decreased and punchthrough would be mitigated and high-electric-field effects would be ameliorated.

asymmetric S,D S should be more heavily doped to reduce and thereby boost the MOSFET on-state current. A heavily doped drain would result in high electric field strength at the drain end of the channel region, resulting in undesirable “hot carrier” effects; it would also worsen the punchthrough problem. Therefore, a heavily doped drain is not desirable.

retrograde channel doping non-uniform doping, concentration is low near the surface and increases with depth into the substrate; 1. Improved mobility; 2. Better short-channel control; 3. Optimized threshold voltage;
